
This is a bare-bones outline of building zebra, since officially it is not
supported, but this might be enough to help someone get started.

Building Zebra from source requires the following, as a minimum:

	A recent GNU GCC (C and C++) compiler

	The netcdf and udunits packages from Unidata
	http://www.unidata.ucar.edu

	X11 and the Athena Widgets library

It is known to build on recent versions of Linux and Solaris and older
versions of Irix and HP-UX.

Edit config/project/config.h according to the instructions found inside,
then run make in the top directory:

	make World >& make.zebra &

